name: LIM CHUN XIN
description:
LIM CHUN XIN, a student pursuing a Bachelor in Software Engineering, shows excellent academic performance with a CGPA of 3.888. LIM CHUN XIN excels at programming and is highly skilled in design, demonstrating outstanding capabilities in these core technical areas. This is further supported by practical experience, having developed computing projects such as 'TypingEducationGame' and 'simple-ai-unity', using languages like C++, PHP, and C#.

LIM CHUN XIN is also competent in IT infrastructure, showing a solid understanding of how systems are built and maintained. Beyond technical skills, LIM CHUN XIN has actively taken on leadership roles. As a Director for the Jarvis Technology Club, LIM CHUN XIN led significant initiatives. This included designing a fairer competition structure, managing participant registrations, and coordinating a team to handle timekeeping, scoring, and technical support for club events. These experiences highlight strong organizational and team management skills.

LIM CHUN XIN is currently developing skills in feedback sentiment and has an opportunity to strengthen professional engagement.
